article.headline: Tennessee Tech 65, Tenn.-Martin 61
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Amadi McKenzie was perfect from the field to score 23 points and lead Tennessee Tech to a 65-61 victory over Tennessee-Martin on Tuesday night. Tech (16-11, 12-6 Ohio Valley Conference) stayed in the running for a top seed in the OVC tourney and have won 10 of their last 12 games. McKenzie was 9-of-9 from the floor and also had a game-high nine rebounds and four steals. Tennessee-Martin (7-22, 5-14 OVC) never led after going ahead 41-40 with 12:59 left, but did tie it 55-55 with 5:59 left. Tennessee-Martin's McClenon Tolliver hit a 3-pointer to make it 63-61 with 33 seconds left, but the Golden Eagles' Anthony Fisher made two free throws for the closing score, the last with seven seconds left. The Golden Eagles shot 63.6 percent in the second half to overcome a 32-25 halftime deficit. The Skyhawks hit just 29.4 percent in the second half.
